WEBVTT

00:01.430 --> 00:03.364
Previously on Elementary...I know you killed Jameel Clark.

00:03.400 --> 00:05.220
WATSON: He's worked for months to embed himself in SBK.

00:05.270 --> 00:06.737
An endeavor I cared more about

00:06.770 --> 00:08.032
before I knew he wasa cold-blooded killer.

00:08.070 --> 00:09.708
SBK is a ruthless drug gang.

00:09.740 --> 00:12.038
(grunts)

00:12.080 --> 00:12.705
SHINWELL: You want to knowwho killed Jameel?

00:12.740 --> 00:14.503
SBK killed Jameel.

00:14.540 --> 00:16.349
You're looking for someonewho killed one person.

00:16.380 --> 00:19.042
SBK kills dozensof people a year.

00:19.080 --> 00:20.069
I'm gonnatake SBK down.

00:20.120 --> 00:22.213
And anybody whoget in my way...

00:22.250 --> 00:26.311
(groans)...gonna get hurt.

00:26.360 --> 00:28.715
HOLMES:It's of the highest importancein the art of detection

00:28.760 --> 00:31.183
to be able to recognize,out of a number of facts,

00:31.230 --> 00:33.323
which are incidentaland which are vital.

00:33.360 --> 00:36.261
In this case, the keyto the whole matter

00:36.300 --> 00:38.097
can be looked forin the scrap of paper

00:38.130 --> 00:39.267
in the deadman's hand.

00:39.300 --> 00:41.336
That little "12"in the corner

00:41.370 --> 00:42.598
matches the numbersin your checkbook.

00:42.640 --> 00:43.834
You wrote that.

00:43.870 --> 00:45.167
GREGSON:More importantly,

00:45.210 --> 00:47.303
you wrote this,

00:47.340 --> 00:49.570
the rest of the letterthe victim was holding.

00:49.610 --> 00:51.271
We found the shreddedpieces of your missive

00:51.310 --> 00:54.575
in New York's Sunset Parkrecycling facility.

00:54.620 --> 00:57.384
My partner spent most oflast night reconstructing it.

00:57.420 --> 00:58.785
I like puzzles.

00:58.820 --> 01:00.788
GREGSON:It's an offer to pay

01:00.820 --> 01:02.356
William Kirwin for his silence.

01:02.390 --> 01:03.687
And a pretty flirty one,

01:03.730 --> 01:05.823
at that.

01:05.860 --> 01:08.397
We figure Kirwin witnessedyou two breaking into the home

01:08.430 --> 01:10.421
of your neighbor, Mr. Acton,

01:10.470 --> 01:12.392
while he was doinghis security patrol.

01:12.440 --> 01:14.761
And, instead of calling it in,

01:14.800 --> 01:16.267
he askedfor a payout.

01:16.310 --> 01:17.561
WATSON: So you luredhim to your home

01:17.610 --> 01:19.202
and shot him.

01:19.240 --> 01:21.231
And tried to make itlook like he was killed

01:21.280 --> 01:22.372
interrupting another break-in.

01:25.280 --> 01:26.872
Alex shot him.

01:26.920 --> 01:28.444
Give me a deal andI'll give you the gun.

01:28.480 --> 01:29.742
June, what the hell?

01:35.720 --> 01:37.381
(phone chimes)

01:40.430 --> 01:43.319
That businesswas a bad one.

01:45.200 --> 01:46.428
Something amiss?

01:46.470 --> 01:48.267
Oh, no, um, it's just my mom,

01:48.300 --> 01:49.562
reminding me about,uh, coffee tomorrow.

01:57.480 --> 01:59.243
(beeps)

01:59.280 --> 02:01.145
Test, test.

02:11.890 --> 02:13.357
(sniffs)

02:13.400 --> 02:14.389
Okay.

02:14.430 --> 02:15.727
You got this.

02:40.720 --> 02:42.278
(rustling)

02:46.560 --> 02:49.154
(squeaking)

03:08.580 --> 03:09.478
Got you.

03:13.990 --> 03:15.958
*

03:23.700 --> 03:25.588
That is curious.

03:25.630 --> 03:29.236
Marcus said the victimhad a paintball gun on her.

03:29.270 --> 03:30.464
Which is odd in itself.

03:30.510 --> 03:32.831
I was commenting onthe nature of the paint.

03:32.880 --> 03:34.677
Paintball pellets

03:34.710 --> 03:36.678
are filled withwater-soluble dyes.

03:36.710 --> 03:38.678
They create bright stains,

03:38.710 --> 03:40.575
but they're still easyto wash off skin and clothes.

03:40.620 --> 03:42.713
But none of this dyecame off on my finger.

03:42.750 --> 03:45.685
This is Disperse Red 9.

03:45.720 --> 03:47.415
That's the stuff indye packs that banks use

03:47.460 --> 03:48.518
when they're beingrobbed, right?

03:48.560 --> 03:49.925
Mm-hmm.

03:49.960 --> 03:51.518
This is the very oppositeof washable.

03:51.560 --> 03:52.925
Anything hit by oneof these pellets

03:52.960 --> 03:54.757
would be stained for days,if not weeks.

03:54.800 --> 03:58.520
Doesn't sound like somethingyou could buy commercially.

03:58.570 --> 03:59.764
Maybe a custom order?

03:59.800 --> 04:02.928
As I said, curious.

04:02.970 --> 04:04.608
Hey.

04:04.640 --> 04:07.768
Body's through here.Ready to take a look?

04:10.650 --> 04:13.346
Unis found her afterresponding to a shots fired.

04:13.380 --> 04:16.281
She took a shotgunblast to the chest,

04:16.320 --> 04:17.548
close range.

04:17.590 --> 04:18.648
Buckshot?

04:18.690 --> 04:21.682
Double-aught.Shooter meant business.

04:21.720 --> 04:24.553
No ID on the body,probably taken

04:24.590 --> 04:27.491
by the killer, so fornow, she's a Jane Doe.

04:27.530 --> 04:28.929
WATSON :So. ..

04:28.960 --> 04:32.020
these are spentpaintball casings.

04:32.070 --> 04:34.493
She fired a paintballgun at someone.

04:34.540 --> 04:37.407
Then her target returned firewith a shotgun.

04:37.440 --> 04:39.670
It's a pity the killeralso took her body camera

04:39.710 --> 04:41.507
or we could've actually seenwhat happened.

04:41.540 --> 04:44.043
How do you know she was wearinga body camera?

04:44.080 --> 04:46.048
This indentation here,

04:46.080 --> 04:47.843
it's the exact size and shape

04:47.880 --> 04:50.678
of a popular body cameraclip-on mount.

04:50.720 --> 04:51.948
Also, this isthe charger

04:51.990 --> 04:53.719
for such a device.

04:53.760 --> 04:55.352
BELL: Well, if you're right,got to think the killer

04:55.390 --> 04:56.789
didn't want toleave behind video

04:56.830 --> 04:58.718
of what he'd done.HOLMES:There's more.

04:58.760 --> 05:02.059
The victim's shirt has absorbedthe blood unevenly.

05:02.100 --> 05:04.898
It's more soaked in areasof excessive wear.

05:04.930 --> 05:07.728
And the wear patternis distinctive.

05:07.770 --> 05:09.635
Hmm. Sort oflike a vest.

05:09.670 --> 05:11.661
HOLMES: I submitthe one which

05:11.710 --> 05:15.578
once abraded the shirt wasof the bulletproof-variety.

05:15.610 --> 05:18.443
It also appears she oftenwore a shoulder holster,

05:18.480 --> 05:20.641
and note her hairstyle--it's off the neck,

05:20.680 --> 05:21.817
and she's notwearing any earrings.

05:21.850 --> 05:23.579
BELL:You know what?

05:23.620 --> 05:25.645
Her fingernails were cut shortand painted a neutral color;

05:25.690 --> 05:27.817
tactical boots;she's law enforcement.

05:27.860 --> 05:30.727
Active, too, or why keep upthe grooming standard?

05:30.760 --> 05:32.751
The FBI's NGI databasehas the fingerprints

05:32.800 --> 05:35.052
of anyone who's ever appliedfor a job in law enforcement,

05:35.100 --> 05:36.920
so it shouldn't take longto get a match.

05:36.970 --> 05:38.494
I'll getsomeone on it.

05:38.530 --> 05:39.633
I should get going, too.

05:39.670 --> 05:41.695
Let me know if you geta positive ID.

05:50.680 --> 05:53.649
Yeah, it's her.

05:53.680 --> 05:56.786
It's Chief Vlasik.

05:56.820 --> 05:58.708
Sorry for your loss.

06:00.690 --> 06:02.487
Any idea what a small-townNew Jersey police chief

06:02.530 --> 06:03.986
is doing running around New York

06:04.030 --> 06:05.429
with a paintball gun?

06:05.460 --> 06:06.654
None.

06:06.700 --> 06:08.850
Choice of weaponry aside,

06:08.900 --> 06:11.460
can you think of anyonewho would've wanted her dead?

06:11.500 --> 06:12.831
No. Nanette wasgood people.

06:12.870 --> 06:14.462
Everyone liked her.

06:14.500 --> 06:17.708
Any chance this wasabout police business?

06:17.740 --> 06:18.707
It's hard see how.

06:18.740 --> 06:19.934
She's out of her jurisdiction,

06:19.980 --> 06:22.869
no gun, no vest, no backup.

06:22.910 --> 06:25.549
Cypress Grove isa quiet town.

06:25.580 --> 06:27.673
She spent most of her timewriting speeding tickets.

06:27.720 --> 06:30.883
How did she seemat the office yesterday?

06:30.920 --> 06:32.785
I hadn't seen herin a couple weeks.

06:32.820 --> 06:35.653
As far as I knew, she wason vacation with the kids,

06:35.690 --> 06:37.453
visiting family in California.

06:37.490 --> 06:39.128
Called her sisteron the way here,

06:39.160 --> 06:41.822
the kids are safe in San Diego,but her sister told me

06:41.860 --> 06:45.569
they all thought the chief wasstill in Cypress Grove, working.

06:45.600 --> 06:46.897
So she sent her children away

06:46.940 --> 06:48.862
and then she liedto them and you

06:48.900 --> 06:50.868
about whatshe was up to.

06:50.910 --> 06:53.834
Was she behaving erratically inthe days leading up to her...

06:53.880 --> 06:55.677
supposed vacation?

06:55.710 --> 06:58.076
Did you noticeany atypical behavior?

06:58.110 --> 07:00.112
A few weeks ago, she, uh, spentan afternoon with her lawyer,

07:00.150 --> 07:01.777
going over some documents.

07:01.820 --> 07:04.687
When I asked what it was about,she dodged the question.

07:04.720 --> 07:06.119
But she seemed...

07:06.150 --> 07:08.880
I don't know... excited.

07:08.920 --> 07:10.421
That's all I got.

07:12.030 --> 07:14.021
(door opens, bell jingles)

07:15.560 --> 07:17.699
You came.

07:17.730 --> 07:19.539
Your text saidit was important.

07:21.740 --> 07:23.207
About me and Sherlock...

07:23.240 --> 07:25.731
If you brought me here toapologize, you can save it.

07:25.770 --> 07:28.000
I know who you are, now.I know what you are.

07:28.040 --> 07:30.008
I'm only here because

07:30.050 --> 07:31.802
I'm a consultant for the police,

07:31.850 --> 07:34.114
and you're an informantinside a gang, that's it.

07:35.180 --> 07:36.169
Then I'll get to it.

07:36.220 --> 07:37.687
I'm hitting a roadblock.

07:37.720 --> 07:39.551
I got a whole lot of evidence

07:39.590 --> 07:42.013
against SBK's rank and file.

07:42.060 --> 07:44.528
But nothing onthe leadership,

07:44.560 --> 07:47.028
the big rollers,'cause I have no access.

07:47.060 --> 07:49.199
What do you mean?

07:49.230 --> 07:51.221
They got me reportingto a lieutenant,

07:51.270 --> 07:53.534
G-Knot.

07:53.570 --> 07:56.038
Real name, DaMarco Bridger.

07:56.070 --> 07:58.209
He won't let his people

07:58.240 --> 07:59.537
meet with leadership directly,

07:59.580 --> 08:01.571
you got to report to him.

08:01.610 --> 08:02.872
So I need him gone.

08:02.910 --> 08:05.174
Not gone-gone,but I need him put away.

08:07.550 --> 08:11.111
If police move onan SBK lieutenant,

08:11.150 --> 08:14.153
they might start to worrythey've been compromised.

08:14.190 --> 08:17.023
They would... if you takehim out on gang business.

08:17.060 --> 08:19.620
Thing is, he got a side job.

08:19.660 --> 08:21.525
Low-rent murder for hire.

08:21.560 --> 08:24.199
I heard a guy had himstrangle his ex-wife,

08:24.230 --> 08:25.299
and another guy

08:25.330 --> 08:27.594
had him run overhis business partner,

08:27.640 --> 08:30.734
and the police didn'tlook at him in either case.

08:32.210 --> 08:33.234
But you're hopingI could tie him

08:33.280 --> 08:34.770
to one or the other.

08:34.810 --> 08:38.701
If you take Bridgeroff the streets,

08:38.750 --> 08:41.844
then I have a direct lineto the top dogs at SBK.

08:41.880 --> 08:45.145
And I can take themdown for good.

08:48.020 --> 08:49.726
We got thesefrom Nanette Vlasik's lawyer.

08:49.760 --> 08:51.728
A contract between Chief Vlasikand your production company

08:51.760 --> 08:53.250
for her to participateon a game show?

08:53.300 --> 08:55.655
Uh, Moving Targets isn't a game show,

08:55.700 --> 08:57.167
it's a competitionreality series.

08:57.200 --> 08:58.827
HOLMES: The term"reality television"

08:58.870 --> 09:00.838
is practically OnNellian,isn't it?

09:02.040 --> 09:03.166
I mean, you takewould-be actors,

09:03.210 --> 09:06.134
you put them inmanufactured situations

09:06.170 --> 09:07.728
and then you carefullyshape a narrative

09:07.780 --> 09:09.270
from hundredsof hours of footage,

09:09.310 --> 09:11.778
all to create suchgroundbreaking fare

09:11.810 --> 09:13.118
as Lil' Catwalk,

09:13.150 --> 09:14.811
Dog Lawyers,

09:14.850 --> 09:16.886
and That's Nasty.

09:16.920 --> 09:19.115
You're entitled to your opinion.

09:19.150 --> 09:20.879
So, from the title of your showand the custom paintballs

09:20.920 --> 09:22.785
found at the crime scene,

09:22.830 --> 09:24.582
I'm guessing it's some kindof people-hunting-people,

09:24.630 --> 09:26.257
Most Dangerous Game kind of thing?

09:26.290 --> 09:28.053
Yeah, it's basicallyhide-and-seek.

09:28.100 --> 09:30.261
We started with 30 contestants,

09:30.300 --> 09:32.791
we give them each the name ofa rival and a paintball gun,

09:32.840 --> 09:34.933
we told them to hunt down,shoot their target,

09:34.970 --> 09:37.234
while avoiding whoevermight be hunting them.

09:37.270 --> 09:39.261
Yeah, the, uh, Disperse Red 9,that was my idea.

09:39.310 --> 09:40.971
Wanted to make sureif someone got shot,

09:41.010 --> 09:42.602
they couldn't justwash away the evidence.

09:42.650 --> 09:44.606
I recorded a segment about it,if you guys want to see it.

09:44.650 --> 09:47.244
Jake isn't just a producer onthe show, he's also the host.

09:47.280 --> 09:50.010
So I'm guessing when someoneeliminates a competitor,

09:50.050 --> 09:52.245
they take on thatperson's target?

09:52.290 --> 09:53.689
Yeah, and onand on until

09:53.720 --> 09:55.608
there's only onecontestant left.

09:55.660 --> 09:57.685
Last one standinggets $1 million.

09:57.730 --> 10:00.824
Well, we're pretty sure NanetteVlasik was wearing a body camera

10:00.860 --> 10:02.862
when she was shot,but it's missing.

10:02.900 --> 10:05.994
I don't suppose there was also afilm crew recording last night?

10:06.030 --> 10:07.861
No, unlike your averagecompetition show,

10:07.900 --> 10:09.128
we don't-we don't haveany film crews.

10:09.170 --> 10:10.637
The competitors,

10:10.670 --> 10:12.160
they shoot their own footageusing the body cameras.

10:12.210 --> 10:14.838
"Reality unfettered,"that's our catchphrase.

10:14.880 --> 10:16.302
We give themcell phones

10:16.340 --> 10:18.979
for emergency contact,but otherwise,

10:19.010 --> 10:20.318
they're on their own.

10:20.350 --> 10:22.215
So how was Vlasikdoing on the show?

10:22.250 --> 10:23.285
Good.

10:23.320 --> 10:25.185
Really good; withher police training,

10:25.220 --> 10:26.983
she'd already eliminatedthree other contestants.

10:27.020 --> 10:28.658
Now, she was, uh...she was looking like

10:28.690 --> 10:30.226
one of our favorites.

10:30.260 --> 10:33.650
A million dollars is a prettystrong motive for murder.

10:33.700 --> 10:35.998
Are you suggesting thatChief Vlasik's last target

10:36.030 --> 10:37.691
is a likely personto have killed her?

10:37.730 --> 10:39.288
BELL: She tags himwith a paintball,

10:39.330 --> 10:42.037
he murders herto avoid elimination.

10:42.070 --> 10:44.868
So who wasChief Vlasik hunting?

10:44.910 --> 10:46.366
JAKE: This is Nanette'scurrent target,

10:46.410 --> 10:48.833
Dr. Charles Eriyo.

10:48.880 --> 10:50.905
He's an ER residentat Chandler Memorial.

10:50.950 --> 10:52.679
DARIA: He's also avegetarian, a church-goer,

10:52.720 --> 10:55.746
and he volunteers with thehomeless in his free time.

10:55.780 --> 10:58.385
We call contestantslike him "Dudleys,"

10:58.420 --> 11:00.308
as in Dudley Do-Right.

11:00.360 --> 11:02.009
Yeah, it's hard to imagine himdoing what you think he did.

11:02.060 --> 11:04.949
We'll give you whateverwe have on him.

11:11.470 --> 11:13.791
Hey.

11:17.440 --> 11:19.260
How is Shinwell?

11:19.310 --> 11:23.178
Excuse me?Shinwell.

11:23.210 --> 11:26.099
Shinwell Johnson.Sleepy-eyed gang informant,

11:26.150 --> 11:28.971
chess aficionado, murderer--ring any bells?

11:29.020 --> 11:30.783
You saw the textI got last night.

11:30.820 --> 11:32.378
I did not.

11:32.420 --> 11:34.012
You and your mothertypically caffeinate

11:34.060 --> 11:35.254
at a coffee shopin Manhattan.

11:35.290 --> 11:37.019
You and Shinwell,on the other hand,

11:37.060 --> 11:39.756
like to meet at acoffee bar in Bergen Beach.

11:39.800 --> 11:41.427
The shop's signature blendhas a high percentage

11:41.460 --> 11:43.997
of Sumatran beans,and that distinctive,

11:44.030 --> 11:45.395
pervasive scentwafted my way

11:45.430 --> 11:46.692
as soon as you took offyour coat.

11:50.010 --> 11:51.500
He said it was important.

11:51.540 --> 11:53.178
I'm not a child.

11:53.210 --> 11:54.768
You needn't keepsuch appointments from me.

11:54.810 --> 11:56.277
A street gangneeds dismantling,

11:56.310 --> 11:59.347
and he is, for better or worse,the best way to do that.

11:59.380 --> 12:01.974
I've come to termswith the situation.

12:05.090 --> 12:06.489
So how's it going here?

12:06.520 --> 12:09.114
Did the police findthat doctor you texted me about?

12:09.160 --> 12:12.049
No. Dr. Eriyo is notanswering the phone

12:12.090 --> 12:13.796
given to him bythe producers of the show

12:13.830 --> 12:16.048
that he and Chief Vlasikwere participating in.

12:16.100 --> 12:18.261
And as it turns out,he's quite skilled

12:18.300 --> 12:19.858
at hiding inan open environment.

12:19.900 --> 12:21.390
That is not surprising,

12:21.440 --> 12:24.307
given what I uncoveredabout him.

12:27.440 --> 12:29.135
All this on Dr. Eriyo?

12:29.180 --> 12:30.772
HOLMES: Turned out to bea bit of a mystery

12:30.810 --> 12:32.300
in his own right.

12:32.350 --> 12:34.375
His official recordis laudable.

12:34.420 --> 12:36.274
He grew up in a Ugandanrefugee camp.

12:36.320 --> 12:38.311
He came to the U.S.when he was 19,

12:38.350 --> 12:40.386
thanks to a church groupsponsorship.

12:40.420 --> 12:42.308
Summa cum laudeat university,

12:42.360 --> 12:43.452
then went on tomedical school,

12:43.490 --> 12:46.482
where he graduatedtop of his class.

12:46.530 --> 12:49.397
He now specializesin emergency medicine

12:49.430 --> 12:51.796
at one of New York'stop teaching hospitals.

12:51.830 --> 12:53.434
I'm sensing a "but."

12:53.470 --> 12:55.836
Well, it's all builton a lie.

12:55.870 --> 12:58.134
The producers of Moving Targets provided us

12:58.170 --> 13:00.502
with all of the footagethey had on Dr. Eriyo.

